        "created_at": "2023-07-22T15:04:43.428Z",
        "cooked": "<p>That might work. If you register on a new device you’ll be unregistered from the other device, but if you disable all data connectivity on the old device before you register the new one then it won’t be able to see that it has been unregistered, so it will continue to operate as if it was still registered and just offline. After 90 days though, the client will expire and you’ll get a notification about needing to update. I think you can still view messages in that case, so it might still be accessible.</p>",
